On Sun, 8 Feb 2004, Jamie Auch wrote:

> I have seen many fabulous floors installed into buses. I would like to put
> in a hardwood floor.  What do I need  for a subfloor and what do you all
> recommend for the floor itself.

No suggestions for the floor, but whatever you do make sure that the area
between your floor and the corrugated metal has good ventilation.
Otherwise the wood will hold water in place and rust things out

George
